[The Argentines are working hard to eradicate this disease and with marked success. The disease has become truly sporadic, and a common history is a failure to wholly or completely vaccinate the herds. When the owners fail to vaccinate or leave out a bunch, it becomes public knowledge when the latter come down with anthrax.

This brings back memories of the problems in the US Dakotas, which are now effectively clear of this disease despite the procrastinators. Our thanks to Ramon for his annual report, and he has our full support and appreciation for his hard work. - Mod.MHJ

